    "body": "If you haven’t already, check out our [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/Expensify/ReactNativeChat/blob/main/contributingGuides/CONTRIBUTING.md) for onboarding and email contributors@expensify.com to request to join our Slack channel!\n___\n\n**Version Number:**\n**Reproducible in staging?:** Needs Reproduction (Reproduction blocked)\n**Reproducible in production?:** Needs Reproduction\n**If this was caught during regression testing, add the test name, ID and link from BrowserStack:**\n**Email or phone of affected tester (no customers):**\n**Logs:** https://stackoverflow.com/c/expensify/questions/4856\n**Expensify/Expensify Issue URL:**\n**Issue reported by:** @danielrvidal \n**Slack conversation** (hyperlinked to channel name): #[Convert](https://expensify.slack.com/archives/C07HPDRELLD/p1773220736936909?thread_ts=1773201569.695189&cid=C07HPDRELLD)\n\n## Action Performed:\n## Description:\nDuring onboarding, the “Get paid back from my employer” option does not work well for BYOC (Bring Your Own Company) users who have not yet been invited to their company’s workspace.\nIn observed Track sessions, users are signing up for Expensify because their employer uses it, but they have not yet received a workspace invitation. When these users select “Get paid back from my employer,” the flow does not properly accommodate their situation.\nMany of these users are simply trying to track expenses or prepare expenses before they are invited, especially if they have a corporate card or are not reimbursed directly through Expensify.\nCurrently, the flow only allows them to skip, instead of allowing them to create a workspace or proceed with expense tracking.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce:\n\n1. Create a new Expensify account without being invited to a workspace\n2. During onboarding, select “Get paid back from my employer.”\n3. Continue through the onboarding flow\n\n## Expected Result:\nThe onboarding flow should support BYOC users who have not yet been invited.\nUsers should have the option to:\nCreate a workspace, or\nContinue with “Track and budget expenses” if reimbursement via Expensify is not applicable yet.\nThe flow should not force users to skip.\n## Actual Result:\nThe “Get paid back from my employer” flow does not properly support users who have not yet been invited to a workspace.\nUsers are effectively forced to skip the step\n## Workaround:\nUnknown\n## Platforms:\nSelect the officially supported platforms where the issue was reproduced:\n- [ ] Android: App\n- [ ] Android: mWeb Chrome\n- [ ] iOS: App\n- [ ] iOS: mWeb Safari\n- [ ] iOS: mWeb Chrome\n- [x] Windows: Chrome\n- [x] MacOS: Chrome / Safari\n\n## Screenshots/Videos\n\nThe link for the full stork is in slack [thread](https://expensify.slack.com/archives/C07HPDRELLD/p1773220736936909?thread_ts=1773201569.695189&cid=C07HPDRELLD)\n\n[View all open jobs on GitHub](https://github.com/Expensify/App/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22Help+Wanted%22)\n\n\n<details><summary>Issue Owner</summary>Current Issue Owner: @sobitneupane</details>\n<details><summary>Upwork Automation - Do Not Edit</summary>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Upwork Job URL: https://www.upwork.com/jobs/~022031871664336616105</li>\n        <li>Upwork Job ID: 2031871664336616105</li>\n        <li>Last Price Increase: 2026-03-11</li>\n    </ul>\n</details>",
