    "body": "If you haven’t already, check out our [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/Expensify/ReactNativeChat/blob/main/contributingGuides/CONTRIBUTING.md) for onboarding and email contributors@expensify.com to request to join our Slack channel!\n___\n\n**Version Number:**\n**Reproducible in staging?:**\n**Reproducible in production?:**\n**If this was caught during regression testing, add the test name, ID and link from BrowserStack:**\n**Email or phone of affected tester (no customers):**\n**Logs:** https://stackoverflow.com/c/expensify/questions/4856\n**Expensify/Expensify Issue URL:**\n**Issue reported by:** @shawnborton \n**Slack conversation** (hyperlinked to channel name): [#Convert](https://expensify.slack.com/archives/C07HPDRELLD/p1773231200641309)\n\n## Action Performed:\n## Description:\nApproval workflow rows can become difficult to scan when many users are listed. Currently, the names appear as plain text, which makes it harder to quickly identify users and visually parse the workflow.\nTo improve readability, we should introduce a small “user pill” component that includes the user’s avatar alongside their name. This will make the list easier to scan and help users quickly recognize approvers.\nAdditionally, when workflows contain more users than can be displayed, the “+X more” indicator should include a tooltip showing the additional users.\nSelecting the “+X more” element should continue to behave as it currently does by opening the full Right-Hand Panel (RHP) with the complete workflow details.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce:\n\n1. Navigate to Workspace > Workflows\n2. Open an approval workflow with multiple users listed\n3. Observe the workflow rows containing several approvers\n\n## Expected Result:\nApprovers are displayed using a user pill component that includes:\nSmall avatar\nUser name\nThis makes workflow rows easier to visually scan.\nThe “+X more” indicator includes a tooltip listing additional users.\nClicking or tapping “+X more” opens the Right-Hand Panel (RHP) with the full workflow, as it currently does.\n## Actual Result:\nApprovers are displayed as plain text, which can be difficult to scan when many users are listed.\n\n## Workaround:\nUnknown\n## Platforms:\nSelect the officially supported platforms where the issue was reproduced:\n- [ ] Android: App\n- [ ] Android: mWeb Chrome\n- [ ] iOS: App\n- [ ] iOS: mWeb Safari\n- [ ] iOS: mWeb Chrome\n- [x] Windows: Chrome\n- [x] MacOS: Chrome / Safari\n\n## Screenshots/Videos\n\n<img width=\"2800\" height=\"1624\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06b4a348-c552-48de-93d6-6963323d06b9\" />\n\n<img width=\"2800\" height=\"1624\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d44be720-fc78-4069-b22d-cc2abab4543a\" />\n\n\n[View all open jobs on GitHub](https://github.com/Expensify/App/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22Help+Wanted%22)\n\n\n<details><summary>Issue Owner</summary>Current Issue Owner: @nyomanjyotisa</details>\n<details><summary>Upwork Automation - Do Not Edit</summary>\n    <ul>\n        <li>Upwork Job URL: https://www.upwork.com/jobs/~022031864010605736142</li>\n        <li>Upwork Job ID: 2031864010605736142</li>\n        <li>Last Price Increase: 2026-03-11</li>\n    </ul>\n</details>",
